    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bundler&lt;/strong&gt; is a dependency management tool for Ruby applications. It ensures that the right versions of gems (libraries) are installed and used in a project. Ruby packages are called Gem. Bundler is commonly used in situations where you need to manage multiple Ruby projects with different dependencies or need to ensure that a project has all the necessary gems with specific versions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
